data.chText: 顺从，顺应（大多数人或社会）；随潮流
data.enText: to behave and think in the same way as most other people in a group or society

data.chText: 年轻人被大力要求守规矩。
data.enText: There is considerable pressure on teenagers to conform.

data.chText: 他拒绝遵从当地的风俗习惯。
data.enText: He refused to conform to the local customs.

data.chText: 遵守，遵从，服从（规则、法律等）
data.enText: to obey a rule, law, etc.

data.chText: 这座建筑物不符合安全条例。
data.enText: The building does not conform with safety regulations.
to agree with or match sth

data.chText: 这和一座常规的工业城市那种千篇一律的格局不一样。
data.enText: It did not conform to the usual stereotype of an industrial city.

simple_means.memory_skill: con 共同 + form 形式 → 共同的形式 → 使一致

ex.enText: This copy does not correspond with the original.

ex.chText: 这些标记与地图上的各点相对应。
ex.enText: The marks correspond to points on the map.

ex.chText: 他对事件的陈述与她说的不符。
ex.enText: His accounts of events do not correspond with hers.

synonyms.bx: 指两个事物或观点在某一方面或内容上互相匹配一致，常后接介词  with/to。

ex.chText: 她那漂亮的言辞与肮脏的行为不相符合。
ex.enText: Her beautiful words and dirty actions do not accord.

ex.chText: 你的行为与你的原则不符。
ex.enText: Your behaviour does not accord with your principle.

synonyms.bx: 常指行为、观点、性格、质量等方面一致，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 几个证人的陈述并不一致。
ex.enText: The witnesses' statements don't agree with each other.

ex.chText: 他的叙述和警方说的不一致。
ex.enText: His story doesn't agree with what the police have said.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指两条信息等相符或一致，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 我的宗教信仰跟你的不同。
ex.enText: My religious beliefs don't coincide with yours.

synonyms.bx: 多指想法、观点等一致或相符，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 我们对安排方面的意见与董事会一致。
ex.enText: Our opinions on the arrangement concur with those of the board.

ex.chText: 关于出口问题，我同意你的看法。
ex.enText: I concur with your opinion on exports.

synonyms.bx: 强调意见一致，一般用于正式场合，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 他的行为与社会习俗相左。
ex.enText: His behaviour doesn't conform to the customs of society.
Do you conform to the traffic rules?

synonyms.bx: 强调一致性，也指遵照已确立的规则或模式行事，常后接介词 to。

tr: adapt or conform oneself to new or different conditions
example: We must adjust to the bad economic situation

tr: be similar, be in line with

value.def: If something conforms to something such as a law or someone's wishes, it is of the required type or quality.

example.ex: The Night Rider lamp has been designed to conform to new British Standard safety requirements...
example.tran: “夜行者”灯的设计符合新的英国安全标准的要求。

example.ex: The meat market can continue only if it is radically overhauled to conform with strict European standards.
example.tran: 肉类市场只有经过彻底的大检查，严格遵守欧洲标准，才能继续营业。

value.tran: 遵守，遵从，符合(法律、意愿等)

value.def: If you conform, you behave in the way that you are expected or supposed to behave.

example.ex: Many children who can't or don't conform are often bullied...
example.tran: 很多不能或不按规矩行事的小孩常常被人欺负。

example.ex: He did not feel obliged to conform to the rules that applied to ordinary men...
example.tran: 他觉得自己不必遵守那些适用于普通人的规定。

example.ex: We conformed with social and family expectations.
example.tran: 我们遵从社会和家庭的期望行事。

value.tran: 按规矩行事;顺从;随潮流

value.def: If someone or something conforms to a pattern or type, they are very similar to it.

example.ex: I am well aware that we all conform to one stereotype or another...
example.tran: 我们所有人都能找到某种与自己相似的模式化形象，这一点我很清楚。

example.ex: Like most 'peacetime wars' it did not conform to preconceived ideas.
example.tran: 如同大多数“和平时代的战争”一样，这与我们的预想不同。

value.tran: (与样式、类型等)非常相似，一致，相吻合
